Subject: [PATCH] BUILD-FIX bump hatchling floor for PEP 639 metadata

filelock 3.12.2 declares `license = "Unlicense"` (an SPDX expression), which
makes hatchling emit a `License-Expression` field. That field is only valid
from Metadata-Version 2.4 onward. hatchling's loose floor here (>=1.17.1)
lets PEP 517 build isolation resolve a transitional backend that emits
`License-Expression` while still stamping `Metadata-Version: 2.1`, producing
metadata that twine rejects on upload:

    InvalidDistribution: Invalid distribution metadata:
    license-expression introduced in metadata version 2.4, not 2.1

Raising the floor to hatchling>=1.27 (the first release that pairs the PEP 639
fields with Metadata-Version 2.4) makes the emitted metadata self-consistent,
matching what filelock 3.18.0 already pins.

--- a/pyproject.toml
+++ b/pyproject.toml
@@ -2,7 +2,7 @@
 build-backend = "hatchling.build"
 requires = [
   "hatch-vcs>=0.3",
-  "hatchling>=1.17.1",
+  "hatchling>=1.27",
 ]
 
